{"questionId":"9086724","questionHtml":"<p>Theory predicts that</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>∝</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>W</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><msup><mi>L</mi><mi>y</mi></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>E</mi><mi>I</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi></math> are constants. The fundamental units of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi></math> are m<sup>4</sup> and those of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi></math>&nbsp;are kg m<sup>−1 </sup>s<sup>−2</sup>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Calculate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>units of <em>W</em> : kg m s<sup>−2</sup> ✓</p>\n<p>work leading to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> ✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9086724","referenceCode":"SPM.1B.SL.TZ0.c","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Theory predicts that d∝WxLyEI where E and I are constants. The fundamental units of I are m4 and those of E are kg m−1 s−2. Calculate x and y.","paper":"1B","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Tools","Tools","Tool 3: Mathematics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}